makediary (0.3.1-1) unstable;

 * Make a two page image optionally show more than half on each page.
 * Handle the transition from PIL to pillow.
 * Fix PDF generation.
 * Command line rationalisation.
 * Fix an error in command line processing.
 * Make the calendar pages optional.
 * Allow specification of a colour for lines and text.

 -- Russell Steicke <russells@adelie.cx>  Wed, 20 Sep 2017 17:20:00 +0800

makediary (0.3.0-1) unstable;

 * Use make to construct the eps files.
 * Let the conversions ref take multiple pages.
 * Minor changes to the personal information page.
 * Allow inclusion of man pages.
 * Add a line to the side of each of the conversions tables.
 * Move the clean-all script into the Makefile.
 * Specify the number of expense pages.
 * Make notes pages optionally gridded.
 * Make the default appointment width work as expected.
 * Correct the counting of weeks after the year.
 * If the cover title is too long, reduce its font size.
 * Allow the cover page title to span multiple lines.
 * Allow removal of title shading for normal days or all days.
 * Put a box around the current month in the work layout.
 * Split makediary.py into class files.
 * Fix an error in the day title shading error message.
 * Make a string class that tells us the file it came from.
 * Add a diary layout without dated pages - a "logbook".

 -- Russell Steicke <russells@adelie.cx>  Mon,  4 Aug 2014 20:30:00 +0800

