makediary (0.2.97-1) unstable; urgency = low

  * Allow using pcal to generate the list of events.
  * Use a more pythonic way of joining a list of strings.
  * Document more of the .calendar differences from pcal.
  * Remove -E from pcal invocation.
  * Create a new layout more suitable for work diaries.
  * Allow opt -A in pcal .calendar files.
  * Add missing comma in usage strings.
  * Hack around the python installation paths.
  * Make calendars on the bottom centred around the current month.
  * Stop printing the usage message unexpectedly.
  * Stop using sys.argv[0] in error messages.
  * Minor changes to the usage message layout.
  * Make sure the image mode is acceptable to the EPS converter.
  * Allow the cover page to be an image.
  * Allow EPS files to span two pages.
  * Corrections to debian/control.
  * Start the month calendars on Monday.
  * Print the 14 possible yearly calendars.
  * Convert docco from perlpod to asciidoc.

 -- Russell Steicke <russells@adelie.cx>  Wed, 16 Aug 2011 21:00:00 +0900

